      "name": "VAD hemolysis model applicability constraint",
      "description": "Model applicability is restricted to centrifugal blood pumps geometrically similar to the FDA generic pump benchmark (impeller diameter 52 ± 2 mm, volute design class: single-curvature). The hemolysis constitutive model (modified Power Law) is validated only for shear stress exposures in the range 0–800 Pa·s for exposure times 0.001–1.0 s. Extrapolation beyond these bounds is explicitly prohibited. Results are applicable only within the declared operating envelope bounds."
    }
  },
