  "hasDecisionRecord": {
    "id": "https://uofa.net/synth/decision/vad-cou2-accepted",
    "type": "DecisionRecord",
    "actor": "https://uofa.net/synth/actor/morrison-credibility-lead",
    "role": "Credibility assessment team lead",
    "outcome": "Accepted",
    "rationale": "All 13 credibility factors assessed with achieved levels meeting or exceeding required levels at MRL 5. The operating envelope is explicitly bounded (flow 2–6 L/min, speed 2400–3600 RPM, hematocrit 35–45%) and validation experiments densely cover all 15 flow-speed combinations within this envelope. Monte Carlo uncertainty quantification confirms NIH predictions fall within combined experimental and numerical uncertainty bounds at all 12 hemolysis comparison points. Discretization error (GCI 3.1%) and model form uncertainty (three constitutive model variants) are quantified and incorporated into the total prediction uncertainty budget. Independent review of simulation setup found no critical errors. The combination of exact geometry match, NIST-traceable test conditions, quantified uncertainty budget, and dense validation coverage within the declared envelope provides sufficient credibility for Class III regulatory submission at MRL 5. Decision: Accepted.",
